279
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,720
I just wanted to repay you.

280
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:53,720
Repay me for what? I only gave you simple advice.

281
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,080
You could've asked ChatGPT.

282
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:58,680
It would've said the same thing.

283
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,000
I guess...

284
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:03,640
ChatGPT isn't as good-looking as you.

285
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:13,160
Come on, let's go. I'm hungry.

286
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,400
Go where? I thought we were going to have a deep talk.

287
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:20,640
We can deep talk while eating something deep-fried.

288
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:21,760
Sounds perfect, doesn't it?

289
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,080
Let's go.

290
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:25,840
No, I don't eat late at night.

291
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,240
Come on.

292
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:29,280
Just skip it for a day.

293
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:32,960
Consider tonight a special night.

294
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,280
Where you don't have to follow the rules.

295
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:36,680
Come on, I'm starving.

296
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,440
Hey! Wait!

297
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:52,560
Does your workplace do not let you eat?

298
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,600
Why do you look so hungry?

299
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,280
They do.

300
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,480
But right before performances.

301
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:01,240
I get nervous so I can't really eat.

302
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:04,840
So.

303
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:06,760
Have you been playing the piano for a long time?

304
00:21:10,120 --> 00:21:11,160
To be honest.

305
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,760
My mother had me learn since I was a child.

306
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:16,920
But professionally only for a few months.

307
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:19,320
But I didn't do it for a living.

308
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:22,160
The money isn't that great.

309
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:24,080
Here, have some.

310
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:27,960
What about you? What do you do?

311
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:32,400
Me?

312
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:37,560
I'm a photographer.

313
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,880
A photographer?

314
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:44,320
Do you shoot people?

315
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,120
Landscapes?

316
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:49,560
Or pets? Something like that?

317
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:54,600
Well, actaully everything that you've mentioned. People, animals, scenery

318
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:59,080
But I prefer photographing people.

319
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:03,400
They have stories that were far more interesting.

320
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:08,680
Then am I interesting enough to be your model?

321
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:13,040
Maybe like this.

322
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,320
Or like this.

323
00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:18,440
Or even like this.

324
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:20,840
What do you think? Am I good enough?

325
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:24,720
Am I?

326
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:25,680
Not yet.

327
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:28,080
I don't know you well enough.

328
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:29,680
So I don't know how interesting you are.

329
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:32,560
That's a bit harsh.

330
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:37,520
So what kind of person is interesting to you?

331
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:42,360
Someone interesting.

332
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:44,960
Doesn't need to try.

333
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:47,720
Just being themselves.

334
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,520
That's enough.

335
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,280
Just being themselves?

336
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:55,200
You said it yourself.

337
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:00,960
Let's keep eating.

338
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:05,640
Excuse me, complimentary fortune cookies from the house. Please, make a wish.

339
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,280
That's cute.

340
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:10,160
You should try.

341
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:11,680
No thanks.

342
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:14,600
Come on just try.

343
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:22,080
I wish you both a good luck.

344
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:23,760
Do you think it'll come true?

345
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:27,360
Whether it does or not just try it.

346
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:35,200
What does yours say? Let me see.

347
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:38,080
Hey, let me see!

348
00:23:38,280 --> 00:23:41,280
Fortunes telling should not be shared. Else it would never comes true.

349
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:43,200
Not always.

350
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:45,160
Share it.

351
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:46,960
I'll show you mine.

352
00:23:47,080 --> 00:23:49,160
No, I don't need to know yours either.

353
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:51,120
So stingy.

354
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:11,640
They have new things today.

355
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,800
Do you come here often?

356
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:18,240
Quite often. Mostly after work.

357
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:21,680
It's relaxing and cheap too.

358
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:26,480
We should come together again sometime.

359
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,320
Who would go out with you again?

360
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:31,920
Once is enough.

361
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:35,680
Fine. Once it is.

362
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:39,560
Then let's make tonight count.

363
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:42,240
There's so much stuff here.

364
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:44,640
The atmosphere really nice too.

365
00:24:48,040 --> 00:24:48,800
Hey.

366
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:49,760
Look over there.

367
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:54,240
That kid plays beautifully.

368
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:57,000
But no one's watching.

369
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:01,560
Looks like he's been playing all night.

370
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:05,920
Do you want to help him?

371
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:07,280
I have some cash.

372
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:09,200
You want it?

373
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:11,040
No thanks.

374
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,560
I think I have a better way.

375
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:35,920
“Let me move a little closer, just a little closer…

376
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:39,720
This small heart of mine longs to care for you…

377
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:43,800
Like a true love…”

378
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:28,080
... I wish to be your one and only"

379
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,440
Thank you.

380
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:37,360
If you enjoyed that, please don't forget to support him as well.

381
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:49,320
Were you secretly taking photos of me?

382
00:26:50,920 --> 00:26:52,240
Not secretly.

383
00:26:53,040 --> 00:26:54,640
I meant to.

384
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:58,400
So does that mean I'm interesting to you now?

385
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:07,640
Besides singing and playing music.

386
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:08,960
What else can you do?

387
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:13,320
A lot. But you'll need time to find out.

388
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:15,480
So just tonight isn't enough.

389
00:27:16,360 --> 00:27:18,160
Let's go over there.

390
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:19,920
Wait.

391
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:35,240
At night is beautiful too.

392
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:37,320
Look at those lights.

393
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:41,640
No wonder you like coming here.

394
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:43,280
It's peaceful.

395
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:44,660
Hey!

396
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:45,520
What?

397
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:46,240
Come here. Quick!

398
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:48,960
Stay here.

399
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:07,560
Come on!

400
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:10,700
Hey!

401
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:12,360
Hurry up!

402
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:13,960
Wait!

403
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:14,540
Wait!

404
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:15,120
Wait!

405
00:28:17,360 --> 00:28:18,160
Are you okay?

406
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:23,040
I'm not. My feet hurt. Why did you bring me here?

407
00:28:27,080 --> 00:28:28,560
Let's go back home.

408
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,240
Wait!

409
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:33,280
Stay a little longer.

410
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:36,920
I don't often have someone to talk to like this.

411
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:42,480
Are you that lonely?

412
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,520
I grew up alone.

413
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:48,040
Not

414
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:50,680
many friends. me.

415
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:54,400
No one really pays attention to me.

416
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:57,320
It feels like I'm alone in this world.

417
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:05,000
I understand that loneliness.

418
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:11,120
I've felt it my whole life.

419
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:16,760
That's why I had to find a purpose.

420
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:20,160
Something that makes my life worth living.

421
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:25,160
I don't know what you've been through.

422
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:28,360
But it must have been hard.

423
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:32,840
Even though we've only known each other for a few hours.

424
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:35,360
But I know you'll get through it.

425
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:50,480
What are you doing?

426
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:51,320
You'll see.

427
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:15,400
I've finally become someone interesting to you.

428
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:32,080
And tonight, neither of us has to be alone anymore.

429
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:40,480
Lyla.

430
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:46,360
I think I should head home.

431
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:47,720
Wait! Already?

432
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:49,540
What's wrong with you?

433
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:52,000
You kissed me.

434
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:54,440
And now you're leaving?

435
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:57,480
I have some work tomorrow.

436
00:31:57,840 --> 00:31:59,360
Goodbye.

437
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:01,360
Hey! Wait!

438
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:03,080
Hey!

439
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:06,640
Are you really leaving me here?

440
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:40,960
Industry insiders all know.

441
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:45,480
This is the first step for anyone who wants to become Petra's partner.

442
00:32:46,560 --> 00:32:49,000
Whoever secures the highlight piece at the auction.

443
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:53,600
Will undoubtedly capture the attention of Petra's CEO.

444
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,800
Miss Key!

445
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,520
Miss Key!

446
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:07,560
Pardon?

447
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:12,520
Are you feeling alright?

448
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:15,680
Or did you celebrate a little too hard with Ai last night?

449
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:19,240
No. I'm fine.

450
00:33:19,280 --> 00:33:21,480
I was just going through what you've said.

451
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:26,200
So, that means our only real competitor is W Empire.

452
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:31,560
But their credibility is significantly stronger than ours.

453
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:39,040
Then, if we win the highlight item,

454
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:44,200
We'll gain leverage when pitching the project, isn't?

455
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:46,480
Yes indeed.

456
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:55,600
Boss, someone is here asking to see you.

457
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,600
Who? I didn't schedule any appointments today.

458
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:00,960
It's the pianist from the jazz bar.

459
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:11,840
Turn her away. Tell her that I'm unavailable.

460
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:20,520
Yes, boss.

461
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:30,440
Who was it?

462
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:34,040
Just a stranger.

463
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:36,040
It's not important.

464
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:47,720
So, she's here, isn't she?

465
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:48,640
Yes madame.

466
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:51,960
That's alright.

467
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:54,280
I'll come back tomorrow.

468
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:56,080
Please let her know.

469
00:34:56,080 --> 00:34:58,080
That people should take responsibility for what they've done.

470
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:01,480
What did she do?

471
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:03,600
She'll understand.

472
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:28,800
Hey!

473
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:06,160
Boss, she's here again. She's been coming back and forth for days now.

474
00:36:07,080 --> 00:36:11,360
It's fine. She'll stop eventually once she gets tired.

475
00:36:21,120 --> 00:36:23,880
"This chance may never come again don't let it slip away."

476
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:30,360
Boss, perhaps you should go see her?

477
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:04,360
How did you know I was here?

478
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:07,760
Your keychain on your camera bag.

479
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:16,920
You claim to be just a photographer.

480
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:20,120
But in reality, you own a racing circuit.

481
00:37:23,160 --> 00:37:24,200
So?

482
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:27,840
I'm not obligated to tell you everything.

483
00:37:28,680 --> 00:37:31,160
Especially not to someone I've only known for one night.

484
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:34,640
And what of it? We've met just one night

485
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:36,920
Does that mean you don't have to take responsibility for what you did?

486
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:40,520
Responsible for what?

487
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:45,400
You were the one who said you wanted a special night.

488
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:47,560
A “special night”?

489
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:51,120
You kissed me and left me alone in the park.

490
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:57,600
That might just be the worst memory I have.

491
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:03,120
So what is it that you want?

492
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:07,040
I want to know you better.

493
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:14,560
You wouldn't be able to handle someone like me.

494
00:38:15,120 --> 00:38:16,640
Do you even know me well enough to say that?

495
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,200
What makes you think I can't handle you?

496
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:28,400
Are you sure about that?

497
00:38:45,240 --> 00:38:47,320
Then don't cry.

498
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:47,920
So how are you holding up?

499
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:51,440
This? Easy.

500
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:54,240
Is it at least a little challenging?

501
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:57,040
A little.

502
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:02,560
Are those tears?

503
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:05,080
Nonesense.

504
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:07,280
You've gone pale.

505
00:40:08,120 --> 00:40:10,400
You're about to faint, and you're still acting tough.

506
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:11,880
Want some inhaler?

507
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:13,000
No need.

508
00:40:14,640 --> 00:40:17,240
I told you I'm not easily afraid.

509
00:40:17,640 --> 00:40:19,480
Do you believe me now?

510
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:24,160
Are you really okay?

511
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:28,720
Let me ask you something honestly.

512
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:30,880
That night.

513
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:34,120
Did you actually feel nothing for me?

514
00:40:37,280 --> 00:40:39,120
Because if you don't.

515
00:40:39,240 --> 00:40:40,760
I won't bother you again.

516
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:42,920
Just don't lie.

517
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:50,200
Maybe… a little.

518
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:54,800
That's why I ran away.

519
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:58,840
Ran away for what then?

520
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:05,160
Why not give yourself a chance to be happy?

521
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:08,720
Don't you want to share the loneliness with me anymore?

522
00:42:36,480 --> 00:42:38,280
Am I good now?

523
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:41,520
I can ride in your race car without throwing up.

524
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:43,840
You're the best.

525
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:48,160
But if you're not feeling well, you don't have to push yourself.

526
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:51,440
I know.

527
00:42:52,240 --> 00:42:55,240
I just want to step into your world a little more.

528
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:59,960
It takes a lot for you to let someone in.

529
00:43:02,720 --> 00:43:04,800
Thank you for trying.

530
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:10,760
But I like you more just the way you are.

531
00:43:11,880 --> 00:43:16,040
Bright and a little mischievous.

532
00:43:16,840 --> 00:43:19,320
The kind of person who tricked me into a date on the very first night.

533
00:43:20,560 --> 00:43:22,440
Well, when I like someone.

534
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:25,000
I must have a plan.

535
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:32,720
But my world isn't meant to be entered.

536
00:43:33,240 --> 00:43:34,360
It's far darker than you'd expect

537
00:43:36,240 --> 00:43:39,240
My world isn't as simple as you might think.

538
00:43:39,720 --> 00:43:43,440
It only started to feel better when I met you

539
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:46,200
You're my first girlfriend, you know that right?

540
00:43:47,360 --> 00:43:48,840
Girlfriend? Already?

541
00:43:49,320 --> 00:43:50,800
It's only been three months.

542
00:43:51,480 --> 00:43:52,280
Why not?

543
00:43:53,120 --> 00:43:56,440
Time doesn't matter as much as feelings do.

544
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:59,320
Are we doing this or not?

545
00:44:03,400 --> 00:44:04,800
Should we?

546
00:44:06,800 --> 00:44:08,600
You still need to ask?

547
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:11,800
I endured all that dizziness riding with you.

548
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:14,680
If we're not dating after this, I'm going to lose it.

549
00:44:16,880 --> 00:44:17,920
Oh really?

550
00:44:18,160 --> 00:44:19,440
I'm dead serious.

551
00:44:22,200 --> 00:44:24,120
Then we're official.

552
00:44:25,320 --> 00:44:27,480
But you have to promise me first.

553
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:30,880
That you'll stay like this in my arms forever.

554
00:44:31,560 --> 00:44:35,400
Hold me tight, for as long as you want.

555
00:44:35,400 --> 00:44:38,400
I promise, I won't throw a tantrum again.

556
00:44:38,640 --> 00:44:40,120
Such a hot temper girl.

557
00:44:40,200 --> 00:44:42,880
You've been like that since day one.

558
00:45:19,680 --> 00:45:21,160
For the past three months

559
00:45:22,320 --> 00:45:24,800
You've grown quite close relationship to that woman, haven't you?

560
00:45:25,240 --> 00:45:27,040
Someone special?

561
